body:
At the moment, the `create` and `remove` methods of `Contents` only accept the fields marked as required by the [Contents API](http://developer.github.com/v3/repos/contents/). Their respective signatures are

```
Content create(
    @NotNull(message = "path is never NULL") String path,
    @NotNull(message = "message is never NULL") String message,
    @NotNull(message = "content is never NULL") String content)
    throws IOException;

Commit remove(
    @NotNull(message = "path is never NULL") String path,
    @NotNull(message = "message is never NULL") String message,
    @NotNull(message = "sha is never NULL") String sha)
    throws IOException;
```

The Github Contents API also allows for the specification of the branch name (`master` will be used if it is unspecified), as well as the committer's name and email address. This is currently not addressed by our API, which means that all `create` and `remove` operations will commit to `master` and will not include any of the committer's details.

It would be good if we can include a `Map` parameter for these optional fields, as per our input parameter design standards ([as seen here](https://github.com/jcabi/jcabi-github/commit/37d3cfd)). The result would be something like this:

```
Content create(
    @NotNull(message = "path is never NULL") String path,
    @NotNull(message = "message is never NULL") String message,
    @NotNull(message = "content is never NULL") String content,
    @NotNull(message= "params is never NULL") Map<String, String> params)
    throws IOException;

Commit remove(
    @NotNull(message = "path is never NULL") String path,
    @NotNull(message = "message is never NULL") String message,
    @NotNull(message = "sha is never NULL") String sha,
    @NotNull(message= "params is never NULL") Map<String, String> params)
    throws IOException;
```

We should update the `RtContents` and `MkContents` implementing classes accordingly. Note that as per our coding standards, `null` should never be used; if the parameters are unspecified, pass along an empty `Map` instance (e.g. `Collections.emptyMap()`) to `params`, in the case you need to do this (for unit/integration testing and so on).

For more details about the two methods above, see ["Create a File"](http://developer.github.com/v3/repos/contents/#create-a-file) and ["Delete a File"](http://developer.github.com/v3/repos/contents/#delete-a-file).
